description:
## Goal

Add comprehensive unit tests for the pure functions in `src/scripts/keyboard-nav.ts` to ensure they work correctly and prevent regressions.

## Test Coverage Targets

Test these pure functions:
- `isTypingContext()` - Detect if user is typing
- `getNextIndex()` - Calculate next index with bounds
- `getPrevIndex()` - Calculate previous index with bounds  
- `getAnnouncementText()` - Extract title for screen reader

## Implementation

Create `src/scripts/keyboard-nav.test.ts`:

```typescript
import { 
  isTypingContext, 
  getNextIndex, 
  getPrevIndex, 
  getAnnouncementText 
} from './keyboard-nav';

describe('Keyboard Navigation Pure Functions', () => {
  describe('isTypingContext', () => {
    it('returns true for input elements', () => {
      const input = document.createElement('input');
      expect(isTypingContext(input)).toBe(true);
    });

    it('returns true for textarea elements', () => {
      const textarea = document.createElement('textarea');
      expect(isTypingContext(textarea)).toBe(true);
    });

    it('returns true for contentEditable elements', () => {
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      div.contentEditable = 'true';
      expect(isTypingContext(div)).toBe(true);
    });

    it('returns true for elements inside .search-bar', () => {
      const parent = document.createElement('div');
      parent.className = 'search-bar';
      const input = document.createElement('input');
      parent.appendChild(input);
      expect(isTypingContext(input)).toBe(true);
    });

    it('returns false for regular divs', () => {
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      expect(isTypingContext(div)).toBe(false);
    });

    it('returns false for null', () => {
      expect(isTypingContext(null)).toBe(false);
    });
  });

  describe('getNextIndex', () => {
    it('increments index when not at max', () => {
      expect(getNextIndex(0, 5)).toBe(1);
      expect(getNextIndex(3, 5)).toBe(4);
    });

    it('stays at max when at boundary', () => {
      expect(getNextIndex(5, 5)).toBe(5);
    });

    it('handles edge case of single item', () => {
      expect(getNextIndex(0, 0)).toBe(0);
    });
  });

  describe('getPrevIndex', () => {
    it('decrements index when not at 0', () => {
      expect(getPrevIndex(5)).toBe(4);
      expect(getPrevIndex(1)).toBe(0);
    });

    it('stays at 0 when at boundary', () => {
      expect(getPrevIndex(0)).toBe(0);
    });
  });

  describe('getAnnouncementText', () => {
    it('extracts title from h2', () => {
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      const h2 = document.createElement('h2');
      h2.textContent = 'Test App';
      div.appendChild(h2);
      expect(getAnnouncementText(div)).toBe('Focused: Test App');
    });

    it('extracts title from h3', () => {
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      const h3 = document.createElement('h3');
      h3.textContent = 'Another App';
      div.appendChild(h3);
      expect(getAnnouncementText(div)).toBe('Focused: Another App');
    });

    it('returns empty string for undefined', () => {
      expect(getAnnouncementText(undefined)).toBe('');
    });

    it('returns Item for element without h2/h3', () => {
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      expect(getAnnouncementText(div)).toBe('Focused: Item');
    });

    it('trims whitespace from titles', () => {
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      const h2 = document.createElement('h2');
      h2.textContent = '  Spaced App  ';
      div.appendChild(h2);
      expect(getAnnouncementText(div)).toBe('Focused: Spaced App');
    });
  });
});
```

## Setup Required

1. Install Jest and dependencies:
```bash
npm install --save-dev jest @types/jest ts-jest @testing-library/dom
```

2. Create `jest.config.js`:
```javascript
module.exports = {
  preset: 'ts-jest',
  testEnvironment: 'jsdom',
  testMatch: ['**/*.test.ts'],
  moduleFileExtensions: ['ts', 'tsx', 'js', 'jsx'],
  collectCoverageFrom: [
    'src/scripts/**/*.ts',
    '!src/scripts/**/*.test.ts',
  ],
};
```

3. Add test scripts to `package.json`:
```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "test": "jest",
    "test:watch": "jest --watch",
    "test:coverage": "jest --coverage"
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 4 pure functions have tests
- [ ] Test coverage >80% for keyboard-nav.ts
- [ ] All tests pass with `npm test`
- [ ] Tests run in CI pipeline

## Estimated Time

4 hours

## Problem

RSS feeds exist (rss.xml, rss/flatpak.xml, rss/homebrew.xml, etc.) but have no validation or testing. RSS is a critical feature for users who want to subscribe to updates.

## Current State

RSS feeds are generated by:
- src/pages/rss.xml.ts (all releases)
- src/pages/rss/flatpak.xml.ts (Flathub only)
- src/pages/rss/homebrew.xml.ts (Homebrew only)
- src/pages/rss/os.xml.ts (OS releases)
- src/pages/rss/verified.xml.ts (verified apps)

**No validation** that:
- XML is well-formed
- Feeds follow RSS 2.0 spec
- Required fields are present
- Dates are in correct format
- Links are absolute URLs
- Content is properly escaped

## Potential Issues

### 1. Invalid XML breaks feed readers
```xml
<!-- Bad: unescaped HTML in description -->
<description>Fix for issue #123 & update</description>

<!-- Good: properly escaped -->
<description>Fix for issue \u0026#123; \u0026amp; update</description>
```

### 2. Relative URLs don't work in RSS
```xml
<!-- Bad: relative URL -->
<link>/apps/org.gnome.Calculator</link>

<!-- Good: absolute URL -->
<link>https://castrojo.github.io/bluefin-releases/apps/org.gnome.Calculator</link>
```

### 3. Invalid RFC 822 dates
```xml
<!-- Bad: ISO 8601 format -->
<pubDate>2026-02-08T20:00:00Z</pubDate>

<!-- Good: RFC 822 format -->
<pubDate>Sat, 08 Feb 2026 20:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
```

## Proposed Solution

### 1. Add RSS Validation Script

Create :
```javascript
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import { DOMParser } from '@xmldom/xmldom';

const rssFiles = [
  'dist/rss.xml',
  'dist/rss/flatpak.xml',
  'dist/rss/homebrew.xml',
  'dist/rss/os.xml',
  'dist/rss/verified.xml',
];

function validateRSS(xmlPath) {
  const xml = fs.readFileSync(xmlPath, 'utf-8');
  const parser = new DOMParser();
  const doc = parser.parseFromString(xml, 'text/xml');

  const errors = [];

  // Check for XML parsing errors
  const parseErrors = doc.getElementsByTagName('parsererror');
  if (parseErrors.length > 0) {
    errors.push('XML parsing error');
  }

  // Check required RSS elements
  const channel = doc.getElementsByTagName('channel')[0];
  if (!channel) {
    errors.push('Missing <channel> element');
  }

  const title = channel?.getElementsByTagName('title')[0];
  if (!title) {
    errors.push('Missing <title> element');
  }

  const link = channel?.getElementsByTagName('link')[0];
  if (!link || !link.textContent.startsWith('http')) {
    errors.push('Missing or invalid <link> element');
  }

  // Check items
  const items = doc.getElementsByTagName('item');
  for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
    const item = items[i];
    const itemTitle = item.getElementsByTagName('title')[0];
    const itemLink = item.getElementsByTagName('link')[0];
    const pubDate = item.getElementsByTagName('pubDate')[0];

    if (!itemTitle) {
      errors.push(`Item ${i}: missing title`);
    }

    if (!itemLink || !itemLink.textContent.startsWith('http')) {
      errors.push(`Item ${i}: missing or invalid link`);
    }

    if (!pubDate) {
      errors.push(`Item ${i}: missing pubDate`);
    } else {
      // Validate RFC 822 date format
      const dateRegex = /^[A-Za-z]{3}, \d{2} [A-Za-z]{3} \d{4} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2}/;
      if (!dateRegex.test(pubDate.textContent)) {
        errors.push(`Item ${i}: invalid pubDate format`);
      }
    }
  }

  return errors;
}

let failed = false;
for (const file of rssFiles) {
  if (!fs.existsSync(file)) {
    console.error(`❌ File not found: ${file}`);
    failed = true;
    continue;
  }

  const errors = validateRSS(file);
  if (errors.length > 0) {
    console.error(`❌ Validation failed for ${file}:`);
    errors.forEach(err => console.error(`  - ${err}`));
    failed = true;
  } else {
    console.log(`✅ ${file} is valid`);
  }
}

process.exit(failed ? 1 : 0);
```

### 2. Add to package.json
```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "validate:rss": "node scripts/validate-rss.js",
    "build": "go run cmd/bluefin-releases/main.go && astro build && npm run validate:rss"
  }
}
```

### 3. Add Online RSS Validation

After deploy, validate with W3C Feed Validator:
```yaml
# In .github/workflows/deploy.yml
- name: Validate RSS Feeds
  run: |
    curl "https://validator.w3.org/feed/check.cgi?url=https://castrojo.github.io/bluefin-releases/rss.xml" | grep -q "This is a valid RSS feed"
```

### 4. Add RSS Tests

Create :
```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { GET } from './rss.xml';

describe('RSS Feed', () => {
  it('should generate valid RSS XML', async () => {
    const response = await GET({});
    expect(response.headers.get('Content-Type')).toBe('application/xml');
    const body = await response.text();
    expect(body).toContain('<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>');
    expect(body).toContain('<rss version="2.0">');
    expect(body).toContain('<channel>');
  });

  it('should have required channel elements', async () => {
    const response = await GET({});
    const body = await response.text();
    expect(body).toContain('<title>');
    expect(body).toContain('<link>');
    expect(body).toContain('<description>');
  });

  it('should use absolute URLs', async () => {
    const response = await GET({});
    const body = await response.text();
    // Check that all links are absolute
    const relativeLinks = body.match(/<link>[^h]/);
    expect(relativeLinks).toBeNull();
  });
});
```

