description:
## Problem

Mobile usability could be improved with larger touch targets and better responsive behavior. Current design works but doesn't follow mobile-first best practices.

## Issues Found

### Touch Targets Too Small

**WCAG 2.5.5 Target Size (AAA):** Touch targets should be at least 44x44px

Currently small targets:
1. **Icon links** (GitHub/GitLab icons): 20x20px (line AppCard.astro:410)
2. **Copy button**: 28x24px (line ReleaseCard.astro:401)
3. **Flathub install icon**: 20x20px (line AppCard.astro:151-161)
4. **Category tags**: Small clickable area
5. **Filter checkboxes**: 16x16px (line FilterBar.astro:154)

### Responsive Layout Issues

1. **Sidebar**: Switches to single column at 1023px, but could use better breakpoints
2. **Stats grid**: 2 columns on mobile causes cramped layout
3. **Release cards**: Horizontal overflow on small screens for long app names
4. **Filter bar**: Takes up too much vertical space on mobile
5. **Featured banner**: Could be collapsible on mobile

### Typography Issues

1. **Body text**: 14px is small for mobile reading (WCAG recommends 16px base)
2. **App names**: Long names truncate without ellipsis
3. **Version badges**: Text is very small (10px) on mobile

## Proposed Fixes

### 1. Increase Touch Targets
```astro
<!-- AppCard.astro -->
<a 
  href={app.sourceRepo.url}
  class="source-icon-link"
  style="min-width: 44px; min-height: 44px; padding: 12px;"
>
  <i class="fab fa-github"></i>
</a>

<!-- ReleaseCard.astro -->
<button 
  class="copy-button"
  style="min-width: 44px; min-height: 44px;"
>
  <i class="fas fa-copy"></i>
</button>
```

### 2. Improve Mobile Layout
```css
/* BaseLayout.astro or index.astro */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .page-layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 10;
    background: var(--color-bg-default);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Collapsible filters on mobile */
  .filters-container {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
  }

  .filters-container.expanded {
    max-height: 1000px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .stats-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* Single column stats */
  }

  .release-name-row {
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  /* Larger base font for readability */
  html {
    font-size: 16px;
  }
}
```

### 3. Fix Text Overflow
```css
.app-name {
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  white-space: nowrap;
  max-width: 100%;
}

.app-id {
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  white-space: nowrap;
  max-width: 100%;
}

.release-summary {
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
  word-break: break-word;
}
```

### 4. Add Collapsible Mobile Filters
```astro
<!-- FilterBar.astro -->
<div class="filters-container">
  <button 
    class="filters-toggle" 
    aria-expanded="false"
    aria-controls="filters-content"
  >
    <span>Filters</span>
    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
  </button>

  <div id="filters-content" class="filters-content">
    <!-- existing filters -->
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  const toggle = document.querySelector('.filters-toggle');
  const content = document.querySelector('.filters-content');

  toggle?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const expanded = toggle.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
    toggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', !expanded);
    content?.classList.toggle('expanded');
  });
</script>
```

### 5. Mobile-Specific Improvements
```css
/* Larger tap areas on mobile */
@media (hover: none) and (pointer: coarse) {
  .app-card,
  .release-card {
    padding: 1.5rem; /* More padding for easier tapping */
  }

  button,
  a {
    min-height: 44px;
    min-width: 44px;
  }

  .category-tag {
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem; /* Larger tags */
    font-size: 0.875rem; /* Easier to read */
  }
}

/* Reduce motion for accessibility */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## Testing Checklist

- [ ] Test on iPhone SE (smallest modern device, 375px width)
- [ ] Test on iPhone 12/13/14 Pro Max (larger phones, 428px width)
- [ ] Test on iPad (768px width)
- [ ] Test landscape orientation
- [ ] Test with Chrome DevTools mobile emulation
- [ ] Test actual touch interaction (not just mouse clicks)
- [ ] Verify no horizontal scrolling on any screen size
- [ ] Test with browser zoom at 200%

## Mobile Breakpoint Strategy

- **xs**: <480px (small phones)
- **sm**: 480-768px (phones)
- **md**: 768-1024px (tablets)
- **lg**: 1024-1280px (small laptops)
- **xl**: >1280px (desktops)

## Benefits

- Better mobile experience (50%+ of traffic)
- Improved accessibility (WCAG AAA touch targets)
- Higher engagement on mobile devices
- Professional mobile UI/UX
- Better conversion for install buttons

## Impact

- No breaking changes
- CSS-only changes (low risk)
- Improves mobile Core Web Vitals
- Better mobile SEO ranking
